      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/4/7/8",
      "text": [
        " الرَّجُلِ يُطَلِّقُ امْرَأَتَهُ وَ هِيَ حُبْلَى قَالَ يُطَلِّقُهَا قُلْتُ فَيُرَاجِعُهَا قَالَ نَعَمْ يُرَاجِعُهَا قُلْتُ فَإِنَّهُ بَدَا لَهُ بَعْدَ مَا رَاجَعَهَا أَنْ يُطَلِّقَهَا قَالَ لَا حَتَّى‌ تَضَعَ‌."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.4794 - Ali ibn Al-Hakam narrated from Muhammad ibn Mansur Al-Sayqal, from his father, from Abu Abdullah (as) regarding a man who divorces his wife while she is pregnant.\nImam (as) said: \"He may divorce her.\"\nI asked: \"Can he take her back?\"\nImam (as) replied: \"Yes, he can take her back.\"\nI asked: \"What if he decides to divorce her again after taking her back?\"\nImam (as) said: \"No, not until she gives birth.\""
        ]
      }
    },
